The President has signed into law S. 2943, the "National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2017." This act authorizes appropriations for Department of Defense programs, military construction, and Department of Energy national security programs for the fiscal year of 2017. It also includes provisions for recruitment and retention bonuses, special payments, and other authorities related to the U.S. Armed Forces. Additionally, the act provides authorities and makes modifications to national security, foreign affairs, and other related programs.